reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Pacifier That Combines Quality and Style
reviews.reviewText: The Playtex Baby Binky Orthodontic Pacifier is an absolute gem when it comes to combining quality, functionality, and style in a baby essential. I can't help but sing its praises for several reasons.The designs of these pacifiers are incredibly cute. The playful blue and orange colors, combined with adorable patterns, make them visually appealing to both babies and parents.I must also mention the thoughtful packaging. The nice box adds an element of elegance and would undoubtedly make these pacifiers an excellent gift choice. It's evident that Playtex pays attention to even the smallest details.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Water will get stuck in nipple if you put in dishwasher; hand wash instead.
reviews.reviewText: I decided to give these a chance for my 8 month old son, he is used to the Nuk pacifiers and these are the same shape. I was surprised that he had no problem switching to these. I like that these have the handle on the top, the Nuk pacifiers that my son uses do not have the handles. It is easy for him to take the pacifier out of his mouth with the handle, so I appreciate that. The quality is nice, the prints are cute and the nipples are orthodontic so better for his teeth as they grow in. I did have the issue with the nipples holding water inside if they're washed in the dishwasher, so I opted to hand wash them to alleviate this problem. I think this 2 pack of pacifiers is affordable, at the current price of $8, and I would buy them again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
